{
  "text": "T f is the filter time-constant. To be used in NCS, discrete-time approximations of the controllers are needed. The proportional part of the PID controller is static and requires no approximation, only sampling. The backward difference method can be used in the approximation of the integral and derivative parts. The discrete-time PID controller algorithm approximating (13) is given in (16) - [CITATION_1] . In addition, the discrete-time approximation of the filter (15) is given in (20).",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "62148674"
